    "what_description": "Arachnothryx stenostachya is a species of flowering plant in the family Rubiaceae, native to Central America and Mexico. It is an evergreen shrub or small tree, growing up to 10 meters tall, with a trunk diameter of up to 20 centimeters. The leaves are opposite, elliptical, and have a length of 4-9 centimeters, with a width of 1-3 centimeters, and are covered with a fine pubescence. The inflorescence is a corymb, bearing small, white or pinkish flowers with four petals, and is followed by a pair of follicles containing seeds. The plant is characterized by the presence of a milky latex and produces a yellowish-brown wood.",
