    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Arachnothryx stenostachya are anti-inflammatory, antioxidant, antimicrobial, and antidiabetic. These properties are largely attributed to the bioactive compounds present in the plant, including flavonoids, which exhibit antioxidant activity by scavenging free radicals and protecting against oxidative stress. Additionally, the saponins found in Arachnothryx stenostachya contribute to its antimicrobial properties, inhibiting the growth of various microorganisms and preventing infections. The volatile oils present in the plant also exhibit antidiabetic properties, potentially lowering blood sugar levels by stimulating insulin secretion and improving glucose uptake in cells. The antiseptic and anti-inflammatory properties of Arachnothryx stenostachya, largely due to the presence of phenolic compounds, make it a valuable natural remedy for wound healing and tissue repair.",
