    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Arachnothryx stenostachya are iridoid glycosides, alkaloids, and phenolic compounds. Iridoid glycosides, specifically arachnothryxin and stenostachysin, exhibit antioxidant and anti-inflammatory activities, which contribute to their potential healing properties. Alkaloids, including stenostachyine and stenostachidine, have been shown to possess antimicrobial and antifungal properties, which could aid in wound healing and infection prevention. Phenolic compounds, such as flavonoids and phenolic acids, have been found to possess antioxidant and anti-inflammatory activities, which could contribute to the plant's potential anti-aging and tissue repair properties. The combination of these constituents may contribute to the plant's potential therapeutic effects, including antioxidant, anti-inflammatory, antimicrobial, and antifungal activities.",
